@prefix : <#> .
@prefix schema: <http://schema.org/> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix onto: <../ontology.ttl#> .

<> a schema:CreativeWork ;
    schema:name "ActivityPub Actor Document Endpoint Source Gate"@en ;
    schema:description "Blocking protocol gate: all ActivityPub endpoint URLs (inbox, outbox, sharedInbox, followers, following) MUST be sourced from the actor document — never guessed by convention."@en ;
    schema:dateCreated "2026-07-09"^^xsd:date ;
    schema:about :actorDocumentGate .

:actorDocumentGate a schema:HowTo ;
    schema:name "How to source ActivityPub endpoint URLs from the actor document"@en ;
    schema:description "The ActivityPub specification requires that all endpoint URLs — inbox, outbox, sharedInbox, followers, following — be read from the actor document. Guessing by appending path segments to the actor URI is a protocol violation. The server's actual paths may differ entirely from the actor URI path (e.g., /DAV/home/{user}/outbox/ vs /dataspace/person/{user}/outbox). Every ActivityPub CRUD operation depends on correct endpoint URLs."@en ;
    schema:step :stepFetchActorDoc, :stepExtractEndpoints, :stepNeverGuess, :stepFailOnMissing .

:stepFetchActorDoc a schema:HowToStep ;
    schema:position 1 ;
    schema:name "Fetch the actor document with content negotiation"@en ;
    schema:text """After resolving the actor URI via WebFinger (self link, type application/activity+json), fetch the actor document:
  curl -skL -H "Accept: application/activity+json" "{actor_uri}"
Follow 303 redirects. The response is a JSON-LD document conforming to the ActivityStreams 2.0 vocabulary, containing all endpoint URLs as top-level properties."""@en .

:stepExtractEndpoints a schema:HowToStep ;
    schema:position 2 ;
    schema:name "Extract all endpoint URLs from the actor document — never use only the actor URI"@en ;
    schema:text """From the fetched actor document JSON, read every endpoint property needed for CRUD operations:
  - outbox      (required for Note, Like, Announce, Follow, Delete, Undo POSTs)
  - inbox       (required for reading delivered activities, verifying delivery)
  - sharedInbox (in endpoints{} sub-object; used for server-to-server delivery)
  - followers   (used for follower collection reads)
  - following   (used for following collection reads)

On Virtuoso ODS instances, these typically live under /DAV/home/{user}/:
  outbox:      https://{host}/DAV/home/{user}/outbox/
  inbox:       https://{host}/DAV/home/{user}/inbox/
  sharedInbox: https://{host}/DAV/sharedInbox/

NOT under the dataspace path:
  https://{host}/dataspace/person/{user}/outbox   ← WRONG (guessed)

The DAV path and the dataspace path are distinct — only the actor document knows the real values."""@en .

:stepNeverGuess a schema:HowToStep ;
    schema:position 3 ;
    schema:name "Never construct or guess any ActivityPub endpoint URL by convention"@en ;
    schema:text """Do NOT construct any ActivityPub endpoint URL by these patterns:
  - {actor_uri}/outbox
  - {actor_uri}/inbox
  - {actor_uri}/followers
  - {instance}/users/{handle}/outbox
  - {instance}/api/activitypub/{handle}/outbox
These are all guesses. The server may use any path structure it chooses. Only the actor document's properties are authoritative. Using a guessed URL leads to silent failures (403, 'Permission denied') that are indistinguishable from ACL issues, wasting diagnostic effort. This applies to all CRUD operations — read (inbox GET), write (outbox POST), delivery verification (sharedInbox), and Follow management (followers/following)."""@en .

:stepFailOnMissing a schema:HowToStep ;
    schema:position 4 ;
    schema:name "If the actor document cannot be fetched or lacks required endpoint properties, stop"@en ;
    schema:text """Do not proceed with any ActivityPub operation if:
1. The actor document cannot be fetched (network error, 404, 500)
2. The actor document response is empty or malformed JSON
3. A required endpoint property (e.g., 'outbox' for writes, 'inbox' for reads) is absent from the actor document
Report the specific failure to the user and do not attempt to guess or fall back to a constructed URL."""@en .
